The number of COVID-19-inflicted deaths in Africa has reached 100,294 on Friday, the Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) said. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases on the African continent also stood at 3,796,354, according to the continental disease control and prevention agencyâ€™s Africa COVID-19 dashboard. South Africa has reported the highest number of deaths related to COVID-19 in Africa, at 48,708, followed by Egypt, at 10,201, and Morocco, at 8,524. The southern Africa region is the area most affected by COVID-19 in terms of the number of confirmed cases, followed by the northern Africa region. A total of 3,346,404 people infected with COVID-19 have recovered across the continent so far, the agency said.